I"ï<h1 id="blockqoutes">Blockqoutes</h1>

<h2 id="syntax">Syntax</h2>

<div class="language-php highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="s2">"qoutes"</span> <span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">boolean</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="nv">$value</span> <span class="c1">// default true</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="description">Description</h2>
<p>Used when you want to reference an external source using quotation marks. You represent any blockquote by preceding the first line of the block quote with a greater-than sign or angle bracket (&gt;). Any defined abbreviation is wrapped in an <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;blockquote&gt;</code> tag.</p>

<h2 id="examples">Examples</h2>

<h3 id="disable">Disable</h3>
<p>Disable blockqoutes:</p>
<div class="language-php highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nv">$Parsedown</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="k">new</span> <span class="nc">ParsedownExtended</span><span class="p">([</span>
    <span class="s2">"qoutes"</span> <span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="kc">false</span>
<span class="p">]);</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
